{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀκολουθ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>follow</b> one, <b>go after</b> or <b>with</b> him, frequently of soldiers and slaves:—mostly with <i>dative</i> <i>person</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 19, etc.; ἀ. τῷ ἡγουμένῳ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 474c; with Preps., ἀ. μετά τινος 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 7.57, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Laches” 187e, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.27, etc.; τοῖς σώμασι μετ᾽ ἐκείνων ἠκολούθουν, ταῖς δ᾽ εὐνοίαις μεθ᾽ ὑμῶν ἦσαν 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 14.15; ἀ. σύν τινι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.5.3; κατόπιν τινός 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 13: rarely with _accusative_, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 558: _absolutely_, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 277e, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 18.8, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. ἐφ᾽ ἁρπαγήν, of soldiers, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.98\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀκολουθῶν, ὁ, as <i>substantive</i>, ={ἀκόλουθος}[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Adul.fragment” 1. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of stars, <b>follow</b> in the diurnal rotation, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Autolycus Astronomus 2.2. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>follow, be guided by</b>, τῇ γνώμῃ τινός[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.38\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῖς πράγμασιν, τοῖς τοῦ πολέμου καιροῖς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.39, 24.95\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>obey</b>, τοῖς νόμοις[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.19: with _accusative_ _neuter_, ἀ. ἅπαντα “PLille” 1.26. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>follow the thread</b> of a discourse, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 107b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of things, <b>follow upon, to be consequent upon, consistent with</b>, εὐλογία.. εὐηθείᾳ ἀ.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “R.” 400e, compare 398d\">Refs</a>]; <b>follow analogy of</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 499a10, +others \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.3.b</b></Level4> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>to be consequent</b>, ὡς γένους ὄντος τοῦ ἀεὶ ἀκολουθοῦντος[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Top.” 128b4\">Refs</a>]; as species to individual, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GA” 768b13. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, ἀκολουθεῖ <b>it follows</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cat.” 14a31.—Not in Trag.: first in 6th c.BC: Hipponax Iambographus 55, with ᾱ (assuming variant)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], elsewhere ; takes place of ἕπομαι in later Greek.","strongNumber":"G0190","accentedUnicode":"ἀκολουθέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1811","matchingForm":"ἐξακολουθέω","stepTransliteration":"exakoloutheō","gloss":"to follow","_zh_tw_Gloss":"隨從","_es_Gloss":"seguir ","_zh_Gloss":"随从"},{"strongNumber":"G1872","matchingForm":"ἐπακολουθέω","stepTransliteration":"epakoloutheō","gloss":"to follow after","_zh_tw_Gloss":"竭力行, 隨著","_es_Gloss":"seguir ","_zh_Gloss":"竭力行, 随着"},{"strongNumber":"G2628","matchingForm":"κατακολουθέω","stepTransliteration":"katakoloutheō","gloss":"to follow","_zh_tw_Gloss":"跟隨, 跟隨著","_es_Gloss":"seguir","_zh_Gloss":"跟随, 跟随着"},{"strongNumber":"G3877","matchingForm":"παρακολουθέω","stepTransliteration":"parakoloutheō","gloss":"to follow","_zh_tw_Gloss":"已緊從, 考察過了","_es_Gloss":"seguir","_zh_Gloss":"已紧从, 考察过了"},{"strongNumber":"G4870","matchingForm":"συνακολουθέω","stepTransliteration":"sunakoloutheō","gloss":"